<doc id="1076001" wikidata="Q7668315" url="?curid=1076001" title="T. Ifor Rees">
<text>Dr Thomas Ifor Rees CMG (16 February 1890 – 11 February 1977) was a British diplomat, author and translator. Born Thomas Ifor Rees at &#x27;Bronceiro&#x27; near the hamlet of Rhydypennau in Cardiganshire, Wales, he served as Britain&#x27;s first Ambassador to Bolivia from 1947 until his retirement in 1949.

He was the author of a number of travel books in Welsh and English, such as &quot;In and around the valley of Mexico&quot; (1953), &quot;Sajama&quot; (1960) and &quot;Illimani&quot; (1964). His translations include a Welsh translation of the &quot;Rubaiyat of Omar Khayyam&quot;, published in Mexico City in 1939.

